[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Ad [Addendum] 49. Witt Library. P.B.II. Outdoor Wedding: A) Borchard type with Old Man coming from the left to the Bride's table; a) 1) [W.] Bringenberg Sale, Müller, Amsterdam, 17-VI-1925, N° 196, Bois 39,5 x 50 cm; 2) The same with trees added left & right, Dr. Lager, London, 17 1/2 x 241/2 in. (adest Burl.Mag.Aug. 1926); 3) like 1) but cut down on left & right. Sale Malmedé & Geissendorfer, Cologne, 14 Nov. 1917, N° 14, 115 x 137 cm; 4) Sale Lepke Berlin 22-II-1910, N° 54, Holz 74 x 106 cm; [blad 2, verso] b) The same composition upright: 1) De Winter Sale, Giroux, Brussels, 12-14 March 1928, N° 29, Bois parqueté 47 x 37 cm (probably identified with picture filed under P.B.I Sale Fiévez, 17-18 May 1923, N° 14, Bois 48 x 37 cm); 2) J. Geoffrey Hart, Esq., Panel 201/2 x 141/4in., Slatter Exh. 1943, N° 9 (colour reprod.); c) Very poor variation on a) with the old man omitted, with different background. My follower of P.B.II. Dunkertz (photograph); [blad 2, recto] Witt L. P.B.II Pesant Wedding outdoor. Th eBorchard type reversed as Munich or Narbonne [...]; [blad 2, verso] [...] b) with one tree on right [...]
